external_knowledge:
- "treasures" refers to software products;
- "most recent gates" represent the latest versions of the software;
- "public" signifies the availability of download for users;
- "adventurers" metaphorically represent the users or consumers who downloaded the software;
- "crossed these thresholds" indicates the action of downloading the software;
- "realm of the latest versions" refers to the latest version of each software product.

sql:
SELECT name, description, category
FROM software
WHERE software_id = 1;

SELECT user_groups.group_name, group_permissions.permission_name
FROM user_groups
JOIN group_permissions ON user_groups.group_id = group_permissions.group_id;

external_knowledge:
'Popular monitoring tools' refers to software products within the 'Monitoring' category;
'A few dozen' indicates a number greater than 60 downloads;
'Sorted by popularity' means ordering by the number of downloads in descending order.

- "Polymaths of the digital world" metaphorically refers to software products that belong to multiple categories;
- "Traversing across multiple categories" indicates that the software products are in more than one category;
- "Downloads their latest version has garnered" refers to the download count of the latest version of the software, where the latest version is indicated by `is_latest = 1`.

sql:
SELECT versions.version_id, versions.software_id
FROM versions
WHERE versions.is_latest = 1;

external_knowledge:
